&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Simon Harmer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Africa&amp;rsquo;s off-spinner Simon Harmer was named ICC Men&amp;rsquo;s Player of the Month for November 2025 for his dominant performances against India in the World Test Championship.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Simon Harmer claimed 17 wickets&lt;/strong&gt; in a two-Test series against India, emerging as the decisive factor.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;His performance guided South Africa to a 2&amp;ndash;0 Test series victory in India&lt;/strong&gt;, their first such series win on Indian soil since 2000.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Harmer was also adjudged Player of the Series&lt;/strong&gt; for his consistent match-winning spells.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;He won the ICC monthly award ahead of Taijul Islam (Bangladesh) and Mohammad Nawaz (Pakistan).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ICC Men&amp;rsquo;s Player of the Month award&lt;/strong&gt; recognises outstanding individual performances across all international formats.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The ICC World Test Championship (WTC)&lt;/strong&gt; is a league-based Test competition that determines the world&amp;rsquo;s top Test-playing nation.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Off-spin bowling&lt;/strong&gt; relies on finger rotation to generate turn, playing a crucial role on subcontinental pitches.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;South Africa&amp;rsquo;s series win in India&lt;/strong&gt; is considered historic due to India&amp;rsquo;s long-standing dominance at home in Test cricket.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Detection of a lemon-shaped exoplanet orbiting a pulsar.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align:middle;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The James Webb Space Telescope has revealed a bizarre lemon-shaped exoplanet located about 2,000 light-years away.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align:middle;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The exoplanet is named PSR J2322-2650b.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It orbits a millisecond pulsar, a rapidly spinning neutron star.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Extreme gravitational forces stretch the Jupiter-sized planet into a lemon-like shape.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The planet is one of the most extreme exoplanets ever observed.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align:middle;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;James Webb Space Telescope (JWST)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; is NASA&amp;rsquo;s most powerful space observatory for infrared astronomy.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The planet&amp;rsquo;s atmosphere is rich in carbon compounds like C2 and C3, with very little oxygen or nitrogen.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;PSR J2322-2650b completes one orbit around its pulsar in just 7.8 hours.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The discovery challenges existing models of planet formation and atmospheric composition.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NCB and RRU.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Narcotics Control Bureau (NCB) and Rashtriya Raksha University (RRU) signed a Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) to enhance cooperation in narcotics control and cyber-enabled drug crimes.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The MoU aims to collaborate on research, technology development, and training in areas like darknet narcotics markets, cryptocurrency tracing, and cyber-threat intelligence.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Both organizations will develop and deliver specialized training programs on cyber forensics, blockchain forensics, OSINT, and behavioral profiling for NCB officers.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A Centre of Excellence in Cybercrime Investigation and Drug Intelligence will be established to foster research and innovation in these fields.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The collaboration seeks to enhance capacity building and innovation in combating cyber-enabled drug crimes.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0); &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Narcotics Control Bureau (NCB)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The central agency responsible for enforcing the laws related to narcotics and combating drug trafficking in India.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Rashtriya Raksha University (RRU)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;An academic institution focused on defense, security, and law enforcement, offering training and research in emerging security threats.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Cyber-enabled Drug Crimes&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Drug-related crimes that leverage cyber technologies, such as darknet markets, cryptocurrency, and digital forensics.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Charles Coste.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The world&amp;rsquo;s oldest Olympic champion, French cyclist Charles Coste, passed away at the age of 101 on October 31, 2025.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Charles Coste was part of France&amp;rsquo;s gold medal-winning men&amp;rsquo;s team pursuit cycling squad at the 1948 London Olympics.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;He carried the Olympic torch as the penultimate torchbearer at the Paris 2024 Olympics opening ceremony.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;He became the world&amp;rsquo;s oldest living Olympic champion after the death of Hungarian gymnast &amp;Aacute;gnes Keleti in January 2025.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Born on February 8, 1924, in Ollioules, France, Coste was also the national pursuit champion in 1947.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-info-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;France&amp;rsquo;s 1948 team included Serge Blusson, Fernand Decanali, and Pierre Adam alongside Coste.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;They defeated Great Britain in the semi-final and Italy in the final to win Olympic gold.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;French judo legend Teddy Riner paid tribute to Coste, recalling receiving the Olympic flame from him at Paris 2024.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;57&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Reducing financial exclusion&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p data-end=&quot;57&quot; data-start=&quot;0&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;200&quot; data-start=&quot;78&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India&amp;#39;s Digital Public Infrastructure (DPI)&lt;/strong&gt; refers to an ecosystem of digital platforms and technologies designed to facilitate public service delivery and financial inclusion.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;400&quot; data-start=&quot;201&quot;&gt;At the &lt;strong&gt;BRICS meeting in 2025&lt;/strong&gt;, a key benefit highlighted was the role of DPI in &lt;strong&gt;reducing financial exclusion&lt;/strong&gt;, ensuring that underserved and marginalized populations have access to financial services. &lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;This statement is correct.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;550&quot; data-start=&quot;401&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial exclusion&lt;/strong&gt; refers to the lack of access to formal financial services such as banking, credit, and insurance. India&amp;#39;s DPI model, through initiatives like &lt;strong&gt;Aadhaar-enabled services&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;UPI (Unified Payments Interface)&lt;/strong&gt;, addresses this challenge effectively.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;700&quot; data-start=&quot;551&quot;&gt;The DPI model integrates digital identity (Aadhaar), payment systems (UPI), and mobile connectivity to create an inclusive financial system. This ensures that even people in rural and remote areas gain access to essential financial services.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;850&quot; data-start=&quot;701&quot;&gt;The success of India&amp;#39;s DPI in reducing financial exclusion has been acknowledged globally, including at international forums like &lt;strong&gt;G20&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;BRICS&lt;/strong&gt;. This makes it a model for other developing economies to adopt and replicate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India&amp;#39;s Digital Public Infrastructure (DPI):&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1000&quot; data-start=&quot;900&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Launched:&lt;/strong&gt; Key DPI initiatives like &lt;strong&gt;Aadhaar&lt;/strong&gt; were launched in &lt;strong&gt;2009&lt;/strong&gt;, while &lt;strong&gt;UPI&lt;/strong&gt; was introduced in &lt;strong&gt;2016&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1200&quot; data-start=&quot;1001&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Components:&lt;/strong&gt; DPI comprises three main components:
		&lt;ul&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Digital Identity:&lt;/strong&gt; Aadhaar, India&amp;#39;s biometric-based unique identity system, enables authentication and financial inclusion.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Digital Payments:&lt;/strong&gt; UPI allows instant, interoperable, and low-cost digital payments.&lt;/li&gt;
			&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Data Empowerment:&lt;/strong&gt; Platforms like DigiLocker and Account Aggregator facilitate secure digital data sharing.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;/ul&gt;
		&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1400&quot; data-start=&quot;1201&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Global Adoption:&lt;/strong&gt; Several developing countries, including &lt;strong&gt;Brazil&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;South Africa&lt;/strong&gt;, are exploring India&amp;#39;s DPI model to address their financial inclusion challenges.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Benefits of DPI in Financial Inclusion:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1500&quot; data-start=&quot;1401&quot;&gt;Enables &lt;strong&gt;direct benefit transfers (DBT)&lt;/strong&gt;, reducing leakages in government subsidies and ensuring timely delivery of funds.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1600&quot; data-start=&quot;1501&quot;&gt;Facilitates access to &lt;strong&gt;banking services&lt;/strong&gt; for underserved populations through initiatives like &lt;strong&gt;Jan Dhan Yojana&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1700&quot; data-start=&quot;1601&quot;&gt;Promotes &lt;strong&gt;cashless transactions&lt;/strong&gt;, reducing dependency on cash and enhancing transparency.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1800&quot; data-start=&quot;1701&quot;&gt;Encourages innovation in &lt;strong&gt;fintech&lt;/strong&gt;, with startups leveraging UPI and Aadhaar for new financial solutions.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Other Options Explained:&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;1900&quot; data-start=&quot;1801&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exporting digital gadgets:&lt;/strong&gt; While India has made advancements in electronics manufacturing, DPI is not directly focused on exporting digital gadgets. Hence, this option is incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;2000&quot; data-start=&quot;1901&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Promoting space exploration:&lt;/strong&gt; India&amp;#39;s achievements in space, such as &lt;strong&gt;ISRO&amp;#39;s Chandrayaan missions&lt;/strong&gt;, are separate from the DPI framework. Hence, this option is incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li data-end=&quot;2100&quot; data-start=&quot;2001&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Increasing tax rates:&lt;/strong&gt; DPI aids in improving tax compliance through digitization but does not focus on increasing tax rates. Hence, this option is incorrect.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/important-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Important Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;UPI Success:&lt;/strong&gt; As of &lt;strong&gt;2023&lt;/strong&gt;, UPI processes over &lt;strong&gt;9 billion transactions&lt;/strong&gt; monthly, showcasing India&amp;#39;s leadership in digital payments.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jan Dhan-Aadhaar-Mobile (JAM) Trinity:&lt;/strong&gt; This trinity connects bank accounts, Aadhaar, and mobile numbers to streamline financial services delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Global Recognition:&lt;/strong&gt; The &lt;strong&gt;World Bank&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;IMF&lt;/strong&gt; have praised India&amp;#39;s DPI model for its role in financial inclusion and poverty alleviation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
